<task id="WCWE-004" project="UI Create Wizard Enhancements R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix overdue badge 400 error — correct sprk_duedate field name</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, bug-fix</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Fix the Quick Summary overdue badge which returns a 400 Bad Request due to an incorrect field
    name (sprk_duedate) in the OData query. The correct field is likely sprk_responseduedatetime on
    the sprk_workassignment entity. Identify the source of the OData query, correct the field name,
    and verify the overdue count displays.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in Fluent UI v9, React, and Dataverse Code Pages</role>

  <goal>
    The OData query for overdue items uses the correct Dataverse field name, returns HTTP 200, and the
    overdue count badge displays the correct number.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">UI code must not hard-code Dataverse entity schemas; use constants or configuration for field names.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006-pcf-over-webresources.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT feedback (E-12) reported that the Quick Summary card's overdue badge shows an error. Network
      inspection reveals a 400 Bad Request caused by referencing sprk_duedate which does not exist on
      the sprk_workassignment entity. The correct field is sprk_responseduedatetime.
    </background>
    <dependencies />
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Locate the OData query">Grep for sprk_duedate across the codebase to find the file(s) containing the incorrect field reference.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify correct field name">Confirm the correct field name is sprk_responseduedatetime by checking entity definitions or other working queries on sprk_workassignment.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Replace field name">Update the OData query to use the correct field name.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Build and verify">Build the affected project and verify no compile errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">File(s) containing the overdue badge OData query (to be identified in step 1)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">OData query for overdue items returns HTTP 200 (not 400).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Overdue count badge displays the correct number on the Quick Summary card.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">grep -r "sprk_duedate" src/ returns zero results (replaced with correct field name).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
